{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779187322846,"sessionID":"ses_1c02c80f1ffeMPOpX92Fqk2guI","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_01_XWvBm6z9XcAOqUZMjWPS7500","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/nestjs/guides/authentication-cookies.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/nestjs/guides/authentication-cookies.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Authentication with HTTP-Only Cookies\n2: \n3: This guide covers the secure authentication pattern using HTTP-only cookies instead of localStorage for JWT tokens.\n4: \n5: ## Why HTTP-Only Cookies?\n6: \n7: ### Security Benefits\n8: \n9: | Feature           | localStorage  | HTTP-Only Cookie  |\n10: | ----------------- | ------------- | ----------------- |\n11: | XSS Protection    | ❌ Vulnerable | ✅ Protected      |\n12: | CSRF Protection   | ✅ N/A        | ⚠️ Needs SameSite |\n13: | Automatic Sending | ❌ Manual     | ✅ Automatic      |\n14: | JavaScript Access | ✅ Accessible | ❌ Not accessible |\n15: \n16: **NEVER use localStorage for JWT tokens.** HTTP-only cookies prevent XSS attacks from stealing tokens.\n17: \n18: ---\n19: \n20: ## Backend Implementation\n21: \n22: ### 1. JWT Strategy (Extract from Cookie)\n23: \n24: ```typescript\n25: // src/core/guards/jwt.strategy.ts\n26: import { Injectable, UnauthorizedException } from \"@nestjs/common\";\n27: import { PassportStrategy } from \"@nestjs/passport\";\n28: import { ExtractJwt, Strategy } from \"passport-jwt\";\n29: import { Request } from \"express\";\n30: import { envConfigService } from \"../../config/env-config.service\";\n31: \n32: @Injectable()\n33: export class JwtStrategy extends PassportStrategy(Strategy) {\n34:   constructor() {\n35:     super({\n36:       jwtFromRequest: ExtractJwt.fromExtractors([\n37:         // First try cookie\n38:         JwtStrategy.extractJWTFromCookie,\n39:         // Fallback to Bearer token (for API clients)\n40:         ExtractJwt.fromAuthHeaderAsBearerToken(),\n41:       ]),\n42:       ignoreExpiration: false,\n43:       secretOrKey: envConfigService.getAuthJWTConfig().AUTH_JWT_SECRET,\n44:     });\n45:   }\n46: \n47:   private static extractJWTFromCookie(this: void, req: Request): string | null {\n48:     const cookieName =\n49:       envConfigService.getAuthJWTConfig().AUTH_TOKEN_COOKIE_NAME;\n50:     if (req.cookies && req.cookies[cookieName]) {\n51:       return req.cookies[cookieName];\n52:     }\n53:     return null;\n54:   }\n55: \n56:   validate(payload: any) {\n57:     if (!payload.id || !payload.email) {\n58:       throw new UnauthorizedException(\"Invalid token payload\");\n59:     }\n60: \n61:     return {\n62:       id: payload.sub,\n63:       email: payload.email,\n64:       role: payload.role,\n65:       firstName: payload.firstName,\n66:       lastName: payload.lastName,\n67:     };\n68:   }\n69: }\n70: ```\n71: \n72: ### 2. SetToken Interceptor (Set Cookies on Login)\n73: \n74: ```typescript\n75: // src/core/interceptors/set-token.interceptor.ts\n76: import {\n77:   Injectable,\n78:   NestInterceptor,\n79:   ExecutionContext,\n80:   CallHandler,\n81: } from \"@nestjs/common\";\n82: import { Observable } from \"rxjs\";\n83: import { tap } from \"rxjs/operators\";\n84: import { envConfigService } from \"../../config/env-config.service\";\n85: \n86: @Injectable()\n87: export class SetTokenInterceptor implements NestInterceptor {\n88:   intercept(context: ExecutionContext, next: CallHandler): Observable<any> {\n89:     return next.handle().pipe(\n90:       tap((data) => {\n91:         if (data?.accessToken) {\n92:           const response = context.switchToHttp().getResponse();\n93:           const authConfig = envConfigService.getAuthJWTConfig();\n94:           const isProduction = process.env.MODE === \"PROD\";\n95: \n96:           // Set access token cookie\n97:           response.cookie(authConfig.AUTH_TOKEN_COOKIE_NAME, data.accessToken, {\n98:             httpOnly: true,\n99:             secure: isProduction,\n100:             sameSite: isProduction ? \"strict\" : \"lax\",\n101:             maxAge: this.parseExpireTime(authConfig.AUTH_TOKEN_EXPIRE_TIME),\n102:             path: \"/\",\n103:           });\n104: \n105:           // Set refresh token cookie (longer expiration)\n106:           if (data.refreshToken) {\n107:             response.cookie(\n108:               authConfig.AUTH_REFRESH_TOKEN_COOKIE_NAME,\n109:               data.refreshToken,\n110:               {\n111:                 httpOnly: true,\n112:                 secure: isProduction,\n113:                 sameSite: isProduction ? \"strict\" : \"lax\",\n114:                 maxAge: this.parseExpireTime(\n115:                   authConfig.AUTH_REFRESH_TOKEN_EXPIRE_TIME,\n116:                 ),\n117:                 path: \"/\",\n118:               },\n119:             );\n120:           }\n121:         }\n122:       }),\n123:     );\n124:   }\n125: \n126:   private parseExpireTime(expireTime: string): number {\n127:     const match = expireTime.match(/^(\\d+)(h|d|m|s)?$/);\n128:     if (!match) return 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000; // Default 24h\n129: \n130:     const value = parseInt(match[1], 10);\n131:     const unit = match[2] || \"h\";\n132: \n133:     switch (unit) {\n134:       case \"s\":\n135:         return value * 1000;\n136:       case \"m\":\n137:         return value * 60 * 1000;\n138:       case \"h\":\n139:         return value * 60 * 60 * 1000;\n140:       case \"d\":\n141:         return value * 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000;\n142:       default:\n143:         return value * 60 * 60 * 1000;\n144:     }\n145:   }\n146: }\n147: ```\n148: \n149: ### 3. Auth Controller (Apply Interceptor)\n150: \n151: ```typescript\n152: // src/modules/auth/auth.controller.ts\n153: import {\n154:   Controller,\n155:   Post,\n156:   Body,\n157:   Get,\n158:   Req,\n159:   UseInterceptors,\n160: } from \"@nestjs/common\";\n161: import { ConfigService } from \"@nestjs/config\";\n162: import { Request } from \"express\";\n163: import { SetTokenInterceptor } from \"@core/interceptors/set-token.interceptor\";\n164: import { RemoveTokenInterceptor } from \"@core/interceptors/remove-token.interceptor\";\n165: import { Public } from \"@core/decorators/public.decorator\";\n166: \n167: @Controller(\"auth\")\n168: export class AuthController {\n169:   constructor(\n170:     private readonly authService: AuthService,\n171:     private readonly configService: ConfigService,\n172:   ) {}\n173: \n174:   @Public()\n175:   @Post(\"login\")\n176:   @UseInterceptors(SetTokenInterceptor)\n177:   async login(@Body() loginDto: LoginDto) {\n178:     // Service returns { accessToken, refreshToken, user }\n179:     return this.authService.login(loginDto);\n180:   }\n181: \n182:   @Public()\n183:   @Post(\"register\")\n184:   @UseInterceptors(SetTokenInterceptor)\n185:   async register(@Body() registerDto: RegisterDto) {\n186:     return this.authService.register(registerDto);\n187:   }\n188: \n189:   @Public()\n190:   @Get(\"refresh-access-token\")\n191:   @UseInterceptors(SetTokenInterceptor)\n192:   async refreshToken(@Req() req: Request) {\n193:     const refreshCookieName = this.configService.getOrThrow<string>(\n194:       \"AUTH_REFRESH_TOKEN_COOKIE_NAME\",\n195:     );\n196:     const refreshToken = req.cookies?.[refreshCookieName];\n197:     return this.authService.refreshAccessToken(refreshToken);\n198:   }\n199: \n200:   @Public()\n201:   @Post(\"logout\")\n202:   @UseInterceptors(RemoveTokenInterceptor)\n203:   async logout(@Req() req: Request) {\n204:     const refreshCookieName = this.configService.getOrThrow<string>(\n205:       \"AUTH_REFRESH_TOKEN_COOKIE_NAME\",\n206:     );\n207:     const refreshToken = req.cookies?.[refreshCookieName] as string | undefined;\n208:     const user = req.user as { id: string } | undefined;\n209: \n210:     if (user?.id) {\n211:       await this.authService.logout(user.id, refreshToken);\n212:     }\n213: \n214:     // RemoveTokenInterceptor clears cookies via ConfigService.getOrThrow — no hardcoded names\n215:     return { success: true, message: \"Logged out successfully\" };\n216:   }\n217: }\n218: ```\n219: \n220: ### 4. Main.ts Configuration\n221: \n222: ```typescript\n223: // src/main.ts\n224: import * as cookieParser from \"cookie-parser\";\n225: \n226: async function bootstrap() {\n227:   const app = await NestFactory.create(AppModule);\n228: \n229:   // Enable cookie parsing\n230:   app.use(cookieParser());\n231: \n232:   // CORS configuration for cookies\n233:   app.enableCors({\n234:     origin: process.env.FRONTEND_URL || \"http://localhost:5173\",\n235:     credentials: true, // Required for cookies\n236:     methods: [\"GET\", \"POST\", \"PUT\", \"PATCH\", \"DELETE\", \"OPTIONS\"],\n237:     allowedHeaders: [\"Content-Type\", \"Authorization\"],\n238:   });\n239: \n240:   await app.listen(3000);\n241: }\n242: ```\n243: \n244: ---\n245: \n246: ## Frontend Implementation\n247: \n248: ### HTTP Service with Cookie Support\n249: \n250: ```typescript\n251: // frontend/app/services/httpService.ts\n252: import axios from \"axios\";\n253: import type {\n254:   AxiosError,\n255:   AxiosInstance,\n256:   AxiosRequestConfig,\n257:   InternalAxiosRequestConfig,\n258: } from \"axios\";\n259: \n260: class HttpService {\n261:   private api: AxiosInstance;\n262:   private isRefreshing = false;\n263:   private refreshSubscribers: (() => void)[] = [];\n264: \n265:   constructor() {\n266:     this.api = axios.create({\n267:       baseURL: import.meta.env.VITE_API_URL || \"http://localhost:3000/api\",\n268:       headers: {\n269:         \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\",\n270:       },\n271:       timeout: 10000,\n272:       withCredentials: true, // CRITICAL: Enable cookies\n273:     });\n274: \n275:     // Request interceptor - NO TOKEN HANDLING NEEDED\n276:     // httpOnly cookies are automatically included\n277:     this.api.interceptors.request.use(\n278:       (config: InternalAxiosRequestConfig) => {\n279:         if (config.data instanceof FormData) {\n280:           delete config.headers[\"Content-Type\"];\n281:         }\n282:         return config;\n283:       },\n284:       (error: AxiosError) => Promise.reject(error),\n285:     );\n286: \n287:     // Response interceptor with token refresh\n288:     this.api.interceptors.response.use(\n289:       (response) => response,\n290:       async (error: AxiosError) => {\n291:         const originalRequest = error.config as InternalAxiosRequestConfig & {\n292:           _retry?: boolean;\n293:         };\n294: \n295:         // Skip refresh for auth endpoints\n296:         const authEndpoints = [\n297:           \"/auth/login\",\n298:           \"/auth/register\",\n299:           \"/auth/refresh-access-token\",\n300:         ];\n301:         const isAuthEndpoint = authEndpoints.some((endpoint) =>\n302:           originalRequest?.url?.includes(endpoint),\n303:         );\n304: \n305:         if (\n306:           error.response?.status === 401 &&\n307:           !originalRequest._retry &&\n308:           !isAuthEndpoint\n309:         ) {\n310:           if (this.isRefreshing) {\n311:             return new Promise((resolve) => {\n312:               this.refreshSubscribers.push(() =>\n313:                 resolve(this.api(originalRequest)),\n314:               );\n315:             });\n316:           }\n317: \n318:           originalRequest._retry = true;\n319:           this.isRefreshing = true;\n320: \n321:           try {\n322:             // Backend sets new cookie automatically\n323:             await this.api.get(\"/auth/refresh-access-token\");\n324: \n325:             this.refreshSubscribers.forEach((callback) => callback());\n326:             this.refreshSubscribers = [];\n327: \n328:             return this.api(originalRequest);\n329:           } catch (refreshError) {\n330:             const authPaths = [\"/login\", \"/register\", \"/forgot-password\"];\n331:             if (!authPaths.some((path) => window.location.pathname === path)) {\n332:               window.location.href = \"/login\";\n333:             }\n334:             return Promise.reject(refreshError);\n335:           } finally {\n336:             this.isRefreshing = false;\n337:           }\n338:         }\n339: \n340:         return Promise.reject(error);\n341:       },\n342:     );\n343:   }\n344: \n345:   // HTTP methods...\n346: }\n347: \n348: export const httpService = new HttpService();\n349: ```\n350: \n351: ---\n352: \n353: ## Environment Configuration\n354: \n355: ### Backend (.env)\n356: \n357: ```env\n358: # JWT Configuration\n359: AUTH_JWT_SECRET=your-secure-secret-key\n360: AUTH_TOKEN_COOKIE_NAME=your-access-token-cookie-name\n361: AUTH_TOKEN_EXPIRE_TIME=24h\n362: AUTH_TOKEN_EXPIRED_TIME_REMEMBER_ME=30d\n363: AUTH_REFRESH_TOKEN_COOKIE_NAME=your-refresh-token-cookie-name\n364: AUTH_REFRESH_TOKEN_EXPIRE_TIME=7d\n365: \n366: # CORS\n367: FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:5173\n368: MODE=DEV\n369: ```\n370: \n371: ### Frontend (.env)\n372: \n373: ```env\n374: VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:3000/api\n375: ```\n376: \n377: ---\n378: \n379: ## Cookie Settings Reference\n380: \n381: | Setting  | Development | Production |\n382: | -------- | ----------- | ---------- |\n383: | httpOnly | true        | true       |\n384: | secure   | false       | true       |\n385: | sameSite | 'lax'       | 'strict'   |\n386: | path     | '/'         | '/'        |\n387: \n388: ---\n389: \n390: ## Checklist\n391: \n392: ### Backend\n393: \n394: - [ ] Install `cookie-parser`: `npm install cookie-parser`\n395: - [ ] Add `app.use(cookieParser())` in main.ts\n396: - [ ] Configure CORS with `credentials: true`\n397: - [ ] JWT Strategy extracts token from cookie\n398: - [ ] SetTokenInterceptor sets httpOnly cookies on login/register/refresh\n399: - [ ] RemoveTokenInterceptor clears httpOnly cookies on logout\n400: - [ ] Logout endpoint uses `@UseInterceptors(RemoveTokenInterceptor)`\n401: \n402: ### Frontend\n403: \n404: - [ ] Axios configured with `withCredentials: true`\n405: - [ ] NO localStorage token handling\n406: - [ ] Token refresh interceptor implemented\n407: - [ ] Redirect to login on refresh failure\n408: \n409: ---\n410: \n411: **Related Guides:**\n412: \n413: - [middleware-guide.md](middleware-guide.md) - Guards and interceptors\n414: - [routing-and-controllers.md](routing-and-controllers.md) - Controller patterns\n\n(End of file - total 414 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Authentication with HTTP-Only Cookies\n\nThis guide covers the secure authentication pattern using HTTP-only cookies instead of localStorage for JWT tokens.\n\n## Why HTTP-Only Cookies?\n\n### Security Benefits\n\n| Feature           | localStorage  | HTTP-Only Cookie  |\n| ----------------- | ------------- | ----------------- |\n| XSS Protection    | ❌ Vulnerable | ✅ Protected      |\n| CSRF Protection   | ✅ N/A        | ⚠️ Needs SameSite |\n| Automatic Sending | ❌ Manual     | ✅ Automatic      |\n| JavaScript Access | ✅ Accessible | ❌ Not accessible |\n\n**NEVER use localStorage for JWT tokens.** HTTP-only cookies prevent XSS attacks from stealing tokens.\n\n---\n\n## Backend Implementation","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude/nestjs/guides/authentication-cookies.md","time":{"start":1779187322569,"end":1779187322844}},"id":"prt_e3fd40922001Out0HWAlg3Pl0y","sessionID":"ses_1c02c80f1ffeMPOpX92Fqk2guI","messageID":"msg_e3fd3d574001l7Qz9YMGbuwjoh"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779187324682,"sessionID":"ses_1c02c80f1ffeMPOpX92Fqk2guI","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_02_oixXBjbeIjY0e1GO8bmE1208","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/nestjs/guides/setup-role-base-access.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/nestjs/guides/setup-role-base-access.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) Setup Guide\n2: \n3: This guide explains how to implement role-based access control for API endpoints in NestJS applications.\n4: \n5: ## Overview\n6: \n7: The application uses a layered authorization system:\n8: \n9: 1. **JwtAuthGuard** (Global) - All routes require JWT authentication by default\n10: 2. **RolesGuard** (Per-controller) - Restricts access based on user roles\n11: 3. **OwnerOrAdminGuard** - Allows access if user is admin OR resource owner\n12: 4. **ResourceAssignmentGuard** - Verifies user has assignment to access a resource (custom)\n13: \n14: ## Core Roles\n15: \n16: Define your application roles in an enum:\n17: \n18: ```typescript\n19: // src/shared/enums/role.enum.ts\n20: export enum RolesEnum {\n21:     ADMIN = 1,\n22:     USER = 2,\n23:     MODERATOR = 3,\n24:     // Add your domain-specific roles here\n25:     // Example: MANAGER = 4, EMPLOYEE = 5\n26:     // Example: SELLER = 4, BUYER = 5\n27:     // Example: INSTRUCTOR = 4, STUDENT = 5\n28: }\n29: ```\n30: \n31: ## Core Decorators\n32: \n33: ### Import Statement\n34: \n35: ```typescript\n36: import {\n37:     Public,\n38:     AdminOnly,\n39:     AdminOrOwner,\n40:     ModeratorOrAdmin,\n41:     RequireRoles,\n42: } from 'src/core/decorators';\n43: ```\n44: \n45: ### Decorator Reference\n46: \n47: | Decorator             | Description             | Use Case                              |\n48: | --------------------- | ----------------------- | ------------------------------------- |\n49: | `@Public()`           | Bypasses authentication | Login, registration, public endpoints |\n50: | `@AdminOnly()`        | Admin role required     | User management, system settings      |\n51: | `@AdminOrOwner()`     | Admin OR resource owner | View/edit own profile                 |\n52: | `@ModeratorOrAdmin()` | Moderator or Admin      | Content moderation                    |\n53: | `@RequireRoles(...)`  | Custom role combination | Flexible access control               |\n54: \n55: ## Usage Examples\n56: \n57: ### 1. Public Endpoint (No Authentication)\n58: \n59: ```typescript\n60: @Public()\n61: @Post('register')\n62: async register(@Body() dto: CreateUserDto) {\n63:     return this.userService.create(dto);\n64: }\n65: ```\n66: \n67: ### 2. Admin-Only Endpoint\n68: \n69: ```typescript\n70: @AdminOnly()\n71: @Get('users')\n72: async listAllUsers() {\n73:     return this.userService.findAll();\n74: }\n75: ```\n76: \n77: ### 3. Admin or Resource Owner\n78: \n79: ```typescript\n80: @AdminOrOwner()\n81: @Get(':id')\n82: async getUser(@Param('id', ParseUUIDPipe) id: string) {\n83:     return this.userService.findOne(id);\n84: }\n85: ```\n86: \n87: ### 4. Custom Role Requirement\n88: \n89: ```typescript\n90: @RequireRoles(RolesEnum.MODERATOR, RolesEnum.ADMIN)\n91: @Delete('comments/:id')\n92: async deleteComment(@Param('id') id: string) {\n93:     return this.commentService.remove(id);\n94: }\n95: ```\n96: \n97: ---\n98: \n99: ## Creating Domain-Specific Roles\n100: \n101: When your application has domain-specific roles (e.g., Manager/Employee, Seller/Buyer, Instructor/Student), follow this pattern:\n102: \n103: ### Step 1: Add Roles to Enum\n104: \n105: ```typescript\n106: // src/shared/enums/role.enum.ts\n107: export enum RolesEnum {\n108:     ADMIN = 1,\n109:     USER = 2,\n110:     MODERATOR = 3,\n111:     // Domain-specific roles\n112:     MANAGER = 4,\n113:     EMPLOYEE = 5,\n114: }\n115: ```\n116: \n117: ### Step 2: Create Composite Decorators\n118: \n119: ```typescript\n120: // src/core/decorators/role-access.decorator.ts\n121: import { applyDecorators, UseGuards, SetMetadata } from '@nestjs/common';\n122: import { RolesGuard } from '../guards/roles.guard';\n123: import { RolesEnum } from '@shared/enums/role.enum';\n124: \n125: // Decorator for manager-only endpoints\n126: export const ManagerOnly = () =>\n127:     applyDecorators(SetMetadata('roles', [RolesEnum.MANAGER]), UseGuards(RolesGuard));\n128: \n129: // Decorator for employee-only endpoints\n130: export const EmployeeOnly = () =>\n131:     applyDecorators(SetMetadata('roles', [RolesEnum.EMPLOYEE]), UseGuards(RolesGuard));\n132: \n133: // Decorator for manager or admin\n134: export const ManagerOrAdmin = () =>\n135:     applyDecorators(\n136:         SetMetadata('roles', [RolesEnum.MANAGER, RolesEnum.ADMIN]),\n137:         UseGuards(RolesGuard),\n138:     );\n139: \n140: // Decorator for manager or employee\n141: export const ManagerOrEmployee = () =>\n142:     applyDecorators(\n143:         SetMetadata('roles', [RolesEnum.MANAGER, RolesEnum.EMPLOYEE]),\n144:         UseGuards(RolesGuard),\n145:     );\n146: ```\n147: \n148: ### Step 3: Use in Controllers\n149: \n150: ```typescript\n151: @ApiTags('Reports')\n152: @Controller('reports')\n153: export class ReportController {\n154:     // Manager creates reports\n155:     @ManagerOnly()\n156:     @Post()\n157:     async create(@Body() dto: CreateReportDto) {}\n158: \n159:     // Employee views their own reports\n160:     @EmployeeOnly()\n161:     @Get('my-reports')\n162:     async getMyReports(@CurrentUser('id') userId: string) {}\n163: \n164:     // Manager views all team reports\n165:     @ManagerOrAdmin()\n166:     @Get('team')\n167:     async getTeamReports() {}\n168: }\n169: ```\n170: \n171: ---\n172: \n173: ## Resource Assignment Pattern\n174: \n175: For scenarios where one role needs access to another's data (e.g., manager viewing employee data, instructor viewing student work), implement an assignment-based access model.\n176: \n177: ### Step 1: Create Assignment Entity\n178: \n179: ```typescript\n180: // src/modules/assignments/resource-assignment.entity.ts\n181: @Entity('resource_assignments')\n182: export class ResourceAssignment extends BaseEntity {\n183:     @Column({ name: 'owner_id', type: 'uuid' })\n184:     ownerId: string; // The user who has access (e.g., manager)\n185: \n186:     @Column({ name: 'resource_owner_id', type: 'uuid' })\n187:     resourceOwnerId: string; // The user whose resources can be accessed (e.g., employee)\n188: \n189:     @Column({ name: 'is_active', type: 'boolean', default: true })\n190:     isActive: boolean;\n191: \n192:     @ManyToOne(() => User)\n193:     @JoinColumn({ name: 'owner_id' })\n194:     owner: User;\n195: \n196:     @ManyToOne(() => User)\n197:     @JoinColumn({ name: 'resource_owner_id' })\n198:     resourceOwner: User;\n199: }\n200: ```\n201: \n202: ### Step 2: Create Assignment Service\n203: \n204: ```typescript\n205: // src/modules/assignments/resource-assignment.service.ts\n206: @Injectable()\n207: export class ResourceAssignmentService {\n208:     constructor(private readonly repository: ResourceAssignmentRepository) {}\n209: \n210:     async isResourceAssigned(ownerId: string, resourceOwnerId: string): Promise<boolean> {\n211:         const assignment = await this.repository.findOne({\n212:             where: { ownerId, resourceOwnerId, isActive: true },\n213:         });\n214:         return !!assignment;\n215:     }\n216: \n217:     async assignResource(ownerId: string, resourceOwnerId: string): Promise<ResourceAssignment> {\n218:         return this.repository.create({ ownerId, resourceOwnerId, isActive: true });\n219:     }\n220: \n221:     async removeAssignment(ownerId: string, resourceOwnerId: string): Promise<void> {\n222:         await this.repository.update(\n223:             { ownerId, resourceOwnerId },\n224:             { isActive: false },\n225:         );\n226:     }\n227: \n228:     async getAssignedResources(ownerId: string): Promise<User[]> {\n229:         const assignments = await this.repository.find({\n230:             where: { ownerId, isActive: true },\n231:             relations: ['resourceOwner'],\n232:         });\n233:         return assignments.map((a) => a.resourceOwner);\n234:     }\n235: }\n236: ```\n237: \n238: ### Step 3: Create Assignment Guard\n239: \n240: ```typescript\n241: // src/core/guards/resource-assignment.guard.ts\n242: @Injectable()\n243: export class ResourceAssignmentGuard implements CanActivate {\n244:     constructor(private readonly assignmentService: ResourceAssignmentService) {}\n245: \n246:     async canActivate(context: ExecutionContext): Promise<boolean> {\n247:         const request = context.switchToHttp().getRequest();\n248:         const user = request.user;\n249: \n250:         // Admins bypass assignment check\n251:         if (user.role === RolesEnum.ADMIN) {\n252:             return true;\n253:         }\n254: \n255:         // Get resource owner ID from route parameter\n256:         const resourceOwnerId = request.params.userId || request.params.resourceOwnerId;\n257: \n258:         if (!resourceOwnerId) {\n259:             throw new BadRequestException('Resource owner ID not found in request');\n260:         }\n261: \n262:         const isAssigned = await this.assignmentService.isResourceAssigned(\n263:             user.id,\n264:             resourceOwnerId,\n265:         );\n266: \n267:         if (!isAssigned) {\n268:             throw new ForbiddenException('Access denied. Resource is not assigned to you.');\n269:         }\n270: \n271:         return true;\n272:     }\n273: }\n274: ```\n275: \n276: ### Step 4: Create Composite Decorator\n277: \n278: ```typescript\n279: // src/core/decorators/role-access.decorator.ts\n280: export const AssignedResourceOnly = () =>\n281:     applyDecorators(\n282:         SetMetadata('roles', [RolesEnum.MANAGER]),\n283:         UseGuards(RolesGuard, ResourceAssignmentGuard),\n284:     );\n285: ```\n286: \n287: ### Step 5: Use in Controllers\n288: \n289: ```typescript\n290: @ApiTags('Employee Data')\n291: @Controller('employees')\n292: export class EmployeeDataController {\n293:     // Employee views their own data\n294:     @EmployeeOnly()\n295:     @Get('my-data')\n296:     async getMyData(@CurrentUser('id') userId: string) {}\n297: \n298:     // Manager views assigned employee's data\n299:     @AssignedResourceOnly()\n300:     @Get(':userId/data')\n301:     async getEmployeeData(@Param('userId', ParseUUIDPipe) userId: string) {}\n302: }\n303: ```\n304: \n305: ---\n306: \n307: ## Controller Setup Patterns\n308: \n309: ### Pattern 1: Resource Owner with Supervisor View\n310: \n311: ```typescript\n312: @ApiTags('Tasks')\n313: @Controller('tasks')\n314: export class TaskController {\n315:     // Employee submits their own task\n316:     @EmployeeOnly()\n317:     @Post()\n318:     async create(@CurrentUser('id') userId: string, @Body() dto: CreateTaskDto) {}\n319: \n320:     // Employee views their own tasks\n321:     @EmployeeOnly()\n322:     @Get('my-tasks')\n323:     async getMyTasks(@CurrentUser('id') userId: string) {}\n324: \n325:     // Manager views assigned employee's tasks\n326:     @AssignedResourceOnly()\n327:     @Get('user/:userId')\n328:     async getEmployeeTasks(@Param('userId') userId: string) {}\n329: }\n330: ```\n331: \n332: ### Pattern 2: Admin-Managed Resources\n333: \n334: ```typescript\n335: @ApiTags('Products')\n336: @Controller('products')\n337: export class ProductController {\n338:     // Admin creates products\n339:     @AdminOnly()\n340:     @Post()\n341:     async create(@Body() dto: CreateProductDto) {}\n342: \n343:     // All authenticated users can view\n344:     @Get()\n345:     async findAll() {}\n346: \n347:     // Admin updates\n348:     @AdminOnly()\n349:     @Patch(':id')\n350:     async update(@Param('id') id: string) {}\n351: \n352:     // Admin deletes\n353:     @AdminOnly()\n354:     @Delete(':id')\n355:     async remove(@Param('id') id: string) {}\n356: }\n357: ```\n358: \n359: ### Pattern 3: Role-Specific Endpoints\n360: \n361: ```typescript\n362: @ApiTags('Dashboard')\n363: @Controller('dashboard')\n364: export class DashboardController {\n365:     // Manager dashboard\n366:     @ManagerOnly()\n367:     @Get('manager')\n368:     async getManagerDashboard(@CurrentUser('id') userId: string) {}\n369: \n370:     // Employee dashboard\n371:     @EmployeeOnly()\n372:     @Get('employee')\n373:     async getEmployeeDashboard(@CurrentUser('id') userId: string) {}\n374: \n375:     // Admin dashboard (all data)\n376:     @AdminOnly()\n377:     @Get('admin')\n378:     async getAdminDashboard() {}\n379: }\n380: ```\n381: \n382: ---\n383: \n384: ## Error Responses\n385: \n386: ### 401 Unauthorized\n387: \n388: - Missing JWT token\n389: - Invalid/expired token\n390: \n391: ### 403 Forbidden\n392: \n393: - Valid token but insufficient role\n394: - Not the resource owner\n395: - Resource not assigned to user\n396: \n397: Example error responses:\n398: \n399: ```json\n400: {\n401:     \"statusCode\": 403,\n402:     \"message\": \"Access denied. Required roles: MANAGER\",\n403:     \"error\": \"Forbidden\"\n404: }\n405: ```\n406: \n407: ```json\n408: {\n409:     \"statusCode\": 403,\n410:     \"message\": \"Access denied. Resource is not assigned to you.\",\n411:     \"error\": \"Forbidden\"\n412: }\n413: ```\n414: \n415: ---\n416: \n417: ## Swagger Documentation\n418: \n419: Add 403 error to ApiSwagger decorator when using role restrictions:\n420: \n421: ```typescript\n422: @ManagerOnly()\n423: @Get('team/summary')\n424: @ApiSwagger({\n425:     resourceName: 'Reports',\n426:     operation: 'getTeamSummary',\n427:     errors: [\n428:         { status: 401, description: 'Unauthorized' },\n429:         { status: 403, description: 'Forbidden - Manager access required' },\n430:     ],\n431: })\n432: async getTeamSummary() {}\n433: ```\n434: \n435: ---\n436: \n437: ## Files Reference\n438: \n439: | File                                           | Purpose                    |\n440: | ---------------------------------------------- | -------------------------- |\n441: | `src/core/decorators/role-access.decorator.ts` | Composite decorators       |\n442: | `src/core/decorators/roles.decorator.ts`       | Base @Roles() decorator    |\n443: | `src/core/guards/roles.guard.ts`               | Role validation guard      |\n444: | `src/core/guards/owner-or-admin.guard.ts`      | Owner/admin check guard    |\n445: | `src/core/guards/resource-assignment.guard.ts` | Assignment validation      |\n446: | `src/shared/enums/role.enum.ts`                | Role definitions           |\n447: | `src/modules/assignments/`                     | Assignment entity/service  |\n448: \n449: ---\n450: \n451: ## Best Practices\n452: \n453: 1. **Use composite decorators** (e.g., `@ManagerOnly()`) instead of `@UseGuards(RolesGuard) @Roles(...)` for cleaner code\n454: \n455: 2. **Apply at method level** for granular control, class level for uniform access\n456: \n457: 3. **Always document** 403 errors in Swagger when using role restrictions\n458: \n459: 4. **Use assignment guards** for hierarchical access patterns (supervisor viewing subordinate data)\n460: \n461: 5. **Keep `@Public()`** only for truly public endpoints (login, register, public content)\n462: \n463: 6. **Delete operations** should typically be `@AdminOnly()` for safety\n464: \n465: 7. **Organize role-specific endpoints** with clear URL prefixes (e.g., `/manager/...`, `/employee/...`)\n466: \n467: 8. **Supervisor-view of subordinate data** should use `/:userId/...` pattern with assignment guards\n\n(End of file - total 467 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) Setup Guide\n\nThis guide explains how to implement role-based access control for API endpoints in NestJS applications.\n\n## Overview\n\nThe application uses a layered authorization system:\n\n1. **JwtAuthGuard** (Global) - All routes require JWT authentication by default\n2. **RolesGuard** (Per-controller) - Restricts access based on user roles\n3. **OwnerOrAdminGuard** - Allows access if user is admin OR resource owner\n4. **ResourceAssignmentGuard** - Verifies user has assignment to access a resource (custom)\n\n## Core Roles\n\nDefine your application roles in an enum:\n\n```typescript\n// src/shared/enums/role.enum.ts\nexport enum RolesEnum {","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude/nestjs/guides/setup-role-base-access.md","time":{"start":1779187324406,"end":1779187324680}},"id":"prt_e3fd410770015scrlxmrKEv7h0","sessionID":"ses_1c02c80f1ffeMPOpX92Fqk2guI","messageID":"msg_e3fd3d574001l7Qz9YMGbuwjoh"}}
